{"id":"259528880_Learning_without_Concentration","abstract":"We obtain sharp bounds on the performance of Empirical Risk Minimization\nperformed in a convex class and with respect to the squared loss, without any\nboundedness assumptions on class members or on the target. Rather than\nresorting to a concentration-based argument, the method relies on a\n`small-ball' assumption and thus holds for heavy-tailed sampling and\nheavy-tailed targets. Moreover, the resulting estimates scale correctly with\nthe `noise'. When applied to the classical, bounded scenario, the method always\nimproves the known estimates.","authors":["Shahar Mendelson"],"meta":["January 2014Journal of Machine Learning Research 62(3)","DOI:10.1145/2699439","SourcearXiv"],"references":["266856478_Learning_without_Concentration_for_General_Loss_Functions","258699533_Minimax_rate_of_convergence_and_the_performance_of_ERM_in_phase_recovery","236871757_Learning_subgaussian_classes_Upper_and_minimax_bounds","38361515_Some_Limit_Theorems_for_Empirical_Processes","38322399_Persistence_in_High-dimensional_Linear_Predictor-selection_and_the_Virtue_of_Over-parametrization","2866564_Local_Rademacher_Complexities","344485423_Concentration_Inequalities_A_Nonasymptotic_Theory_of_Independence","279374141_Upper_and_Lower_Bounds_for_Stochastic_Processes","279355808_Probability_in_Banach_Spaces","267771934_2008_Saint_Flour_Lectures_Oracle_Inequalities_in_Empirical_Risk_Minimization_and_Sparse_Recovery_Problems","267677183_Oracle_inequalities_in_empirical_risk_minimization_and_sparse_recovery_problems_Ecole_d'Ete_de_Probabilites_de_Saint-Flour_XXXVIII-2008","266966324_Probability_in_Banach_spaces_Isoperimetry_and_processes_Reprint_of_the_1991_hardback_ed","266909213_Upper_and_lower_bounds_for_stochastic_processes_Modern_methods_and_classical_problems","266704412_Interactions_between_compressed_sensing_random_matrices_and_high_dimensional_geometry","265996743_Weak_convergence_of_smoothed_empirical_processes","265489908_